        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 9:19PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 919 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Sharon to Marengo to near Maple Park.
Movement was northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of up to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Oakwood Hills, Algonquin, Lily Lake, Woodstock, West Dundee,
Ridgefield, South Elgin, Garden Prairie, Chemung, Huntley, Greenwood,
Gilberts, Lakewood, Marengo, Crystal Lake, Sleepy Hollow, Richmond,
Capron, Carpentersville, Spring Grove, McCullom Lake, Union, Harvard,
Campton Hills, and Hebron.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
north central Illinois.</instruction>
